Functional Responsibility: Security Specialists apply their strong analytical and technical skills to assist in implementing business security solutions. Security Specialists are directed to exercise core skills on projects, or they may direct small teams. They may have such core skills as application development, security assessment, business process designs, or technology architecture. Perform support design, creation, and development of security systems, policies and designs. Minimum Education: Bachelor's Degree in related field.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: Four (4) years of direct related experience in this field may be substituted in lieu of degree.
